quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  4,71,"O believers! Prepare yourselves for encounter, then advance in detachments or all together as the occasion may require"
  4,72,"There will be someone among you who will surely lag behind, so that if you face any calamity, he will say: \"Allah has been gracious to me that I did not accompany them"
  4,73,"But if you are blessed with grace from Allah, he will say, as if there was no friendship between you and him: \"I wish I had been with them; I could have attained a mighty good fortune"
  4,74,"Let it be known that only those people should fight in the cause of Allah who are willing to exchange the life of this world for the Hereafter; and whoever fights for the cause of Allah, whether he dies or is victorious, will soon be granted a mighty reward"
  4,75,"And what reason do you have not to fight in the cause of Allah, to rescue the helpless oppressed old men, women, and children who are crying: \"Our Lord! Deliver us from this town whose people are oppressors; send us a protector by Your grace and send us a helper from Your presence"
  4,76,"Those who are believers fight in the cause of Allah and those who are unbelievers fight in the cause of Taghut (forces of Satan): so fight against the helpers of Satan; surely, Satan’s crafty schemes are very weak"